
Accounting Flow (Core Idea)
Voucher → Journal → Ledger → Trial Balance → Financial Statements
Voucher → Journal → Ledger → Trial Balance → Profit & Loss → Balance Sheet.

1. Voucher
Definition:
Document that proves a transaction occurred.
Purpose:
Source of accounting entry.
Examples
Sales Voucher
Purchase Voucher
Receipt Voucher
Payment Voucher
Contra Voucher
Journal Voucher
Debit Note
Credit Note
Tax Invoice
Key Point
Proof of transaction

2. Journal
Definition:
Book where transactions are first recorded with debit and credit.
Purpose:
Convert voucher into accounting entry.
Format
| Date | Account | Debit | Credit |
Example
Account	Debit	Credit
Cash	5,000	
Sales		5,000
Key Point
First recording of transaction

3. Ledger
Definition:
Book where journal entries are classified by account.
Purpose:
Shows balance of each account.
Examples
Cash Ledger
Bank Ledger
Sales Ledger
Purchase Ledger
Customer Ledger
Supplier Ledger
Key Point
Account-wise summary
Relationship (1 Sentence)
Voucher creates Journal entry → Journal posts to Ledger → Ledger forms financial reports.
Simple Memory Trick
VJL Rule
V → Voucher (Proof)
J → Journal (Record)
L → Ledger (Summary)
One Example
Transaction: Sold goods Rs 10,000.

Voucher
Sales Voucher

Journal
Debit Cash 10,000
Credit Sales 10,000

Ledger
Cash Ledger → +10,000
Sales Ledger → +10,000
